the group based on what would be most useful—they typically prefer updates only when there are actual failures or critical changes. Since the pipeline is healthy and no blockers exist, I should focus on whether this single session resumption warrants group notification or if it's better handled quietly. I'm deciding whether to send a change report or stay silent based on what's actually changed. The only real shift is the Lead's Telegram session resuming work after the Daily Briefing triggered it. Since that report already went to the group, sending another update about session activity feels redundant—the pipeline is running fine and there are no blockers.\n\nWait, I need to clarify what this specific cron job is for. It's labeled as the DTLX progress reporter, so I should verify what it's actually monitoring before deciding whether to stay quiet or send a brief note.","thinkingSignature":"bd714cc32e5932bdcba176743893286007d0329bfba9fc8ac22f05ca5bef1e79"},{"type":"text","text":"Memory is disabled; checking baseline from session transcript history instead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wjc79walv06s_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258","limit":4}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30192,"output":649,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":407,"totalTokens":45192,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776235538243,"responseId":"062e67135b04df6fe65bdb4461596f2c"}}
