{"type":"message","id":"30c079b8","parentId":"87c1952f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:46:20.608Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The last group message was at 05:18 UTC (from cron:ed2d0b5d, the QLHV monitor). The last message from cron:6f3323ef (DTLX monitor) was at 05:09 UTC.\n\nNow comparing the baseline (05:09/05:18 UTC) vs now (06:44 UTC):\n\n**Baseline (05:18 UTC most recent):**\n- QLHV 5p (cron:ed2d0b5d) ✅ running\n- DTLX 5p (cron:6f3323ef) ✅ running\n- Agent Status (cron:e7885813) ✅ running\n\n\n- Lead direct (telegram:direct:6053576134) was running at 05:09\n\nThe pipeline's been stable for over an hour now—all three cron jobs remain healthy, and the Telegram delivery that was previously unstable has been solid since yesterday. There's one minor thing: the DTLX 5p monitor reported its cycle completion at 05:09, but I'm noticing something I need to verify there.\n\nActually, wait—looking back at the main session transcript, the Lead's Telegram session did show as \"done\" from 05:35 onward, but now at 06:44 it's back to \"running\" with activity logged at 06:39. So it cycled through done and came back online. This could mean either a heartbeat refreshed it or it genuinely picked up new work.\n\nThe Daily Briefing cron running at 06:16 UTC is what likely triggered it back into active status. That session's been busy with README edits and project cleanup, but nothing that would constitute a real failure or blocker—just normal operational work. Since there's no actual breakdown or new blocker to report, I'm staying silent.","thinkingSignature":"b1724f5578a16b501a43e5fb3d1416c85be3dd5b4365151c7fc039d799c1d233"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (06:44 UTC) against baseline (05:18 UTC — last group message):\n\n**Active sessions:**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) ✅ running — unchanged\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p) ✅ running — unchanged\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) ✅ running — unchanged\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` (Lead) — was \"done\" (05:35 UTC), now \"running\" (06:39 UTC) — resumed normally after Daily Briefing triggered new work\n\n**Failures:** 0 new\n**Blockers:** none\n**MCP:** all healthy\n\nThe Lead direct session resuming is expected behavior after the Daily Briefing cycle. No failures, no blockers, no new sessions spawned. Pipeline stable.\n\n**SILENT.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1143,"output":560,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":30823,"totalTokens":46790,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776235560793,"responseId":"062e6729d2a99fb82bc5ea4dd93194d9"}}
